      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. it just feels like the school is presenting it as if there's only one way to look at it, and anyone who disagrees is just being \"uneducated\" or something. if the school's goal is to be \"inclusive,\" why wouldn't that include being inclusive of the parents' views too? it feels like one side is being treated as the \"correct\" scientific/social progress and the other is just being labeled as an obstacle. how do you see that balance working?",
